  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposed substation by reason of its combined siting and design would result in an prominent, visually intrusive, incongruous and unsympathetic form of development at street level to the detriment of the visual amenity of the host property, and the surrounding area. The scheme would be contrary to the London Plan 2021 design policies D1, D4, Sites and Policies Plan 2014 Policies DMD2 and DMD3, and Merton Core Strategy 2011 policy CS 14. ",
    "Reason : 2 - The proposed substation by reason of its combined siting, design, depth and height would result in a visually intrusive form of development to the northwest ground floor flat no.1 Rose Court. The scheme is contrary to the Sites and Policies Plan 2014 policies DM D2, DM D3. ",
    "Reason : 3 - The application for the proposed substation has failed to demonstrated that the combined siting, design, and depth would not would result in damage to protected trees by Tree Preservation Order sited in the vicinity. The scheme is contrary to the London Plan 2021 policy G7, LBM Core Strategy 2011 policy CS 13, Sites and Policies Plan 2014 policies DM D1 and O2. ",
    "Reason : 4 - INFORMATIVE\r\nNote to Applicant\r\nIn accordance with paragraph 38 of the NPPF, The London Borough of Merton  (LBM) takes a positive and proactive approach to development proposals focused on solutions. LBM works with applicants/agents in a positive and proactive manner by:\r\n\"\tOffering a pre-application advice and duty desk service. \r\n\"\tWhere possible, suggesting solutions to secure a successful outcome.\r\n\"\tAs appropriate, updating applicants/agents of any issues that may arise in the processing of their application.\r\nIn this instance:\r\n\"\tThe application was not considered to comply with the provisions of the Development Plan and NPPF as submitted, and would have required substantial changes such that a new application would be required. \r\n\"\tThe applicant is advised to seek pre-application advice on any resubmission.\r\n"
  ],
